description: a(0) = 1; a(n) = (1 + a(0)^3 + ... + a(n-1)^3)/n (not always integral!).
comments: Guy states that by computing the sequence modulo 89 it is easy to show that a(89) is not integral. - _T. D. Noe_, Sep 17 2007
references: N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
links: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=0..9
R. K. Guy, The strong law of small numbers. Amer. Math. Monthly 95 (1988), no. 8, 697-712.
N. Lygeros & M. Mizony, Study of primality of terms of a_k(n)=(1+(sum from 1 to n-1)(a_k(i)^k))/(n-1) [dead link]
